es large robust\ncontrollable circuits, capable of multiplexing and transfer learning. Our study\nsuggests that network-based computations of steady-state functions,\nrepresenting either cellular modules of cell-to-cell communication networks or\ninternal molecular circuits communicating within a cell, could be a powerful\nmodel for biologically inspired computing. This complements conceptualizations\nsuch as attractor based models, or reservoir computing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2018 01:36:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Nov 2019 02:51:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-05"}
